Experience an enchanting evening at The Backroom Steakhouse every Saturday from 6:30-8:30pm, where magic and exquisite dining collide. Magician Michael Eaton, who first fell in love with magic as a young boy watching Johnny Carson, will mesmerize you with his world-class skills.
Having honed his craft inspired by legends like David Copperfield, Michael turned his childhood passion into a successful career by the age of 16. Not only that, but he also served as the official magician for the Orlando Magic NBA team from 2009 to 2015, even pulling off the astonishing feat of making Dwight Howard disappear (yes, really).
Michael finds joy in using his abilities to transport audiences back to a time of wonder and imagination. Today, he continues to amaze select clients while also running a digital marketing and design business and cherishing time with his family in Apopka.
Join us for an evening filled with wonder, delicious food, and the spellbinding magic of Michael Eaton at The Backroom Steakhouse.
Every Saturday Night, 6:30-8:30PM
Magic Mike
Book A Table
Excitement fills the air as we announce the upcoming performance of the incredibly talented singer and musician, Krista Prado, at The Backroom.
Krista, a seasoned Registered Nurse, spends her days working in a Post Anesthesia Care Unit. But when she's not tending to patients, she's busy pursuing her passion for music (since the 1980s). Alongside her husband Dennie, who joined her musical journey in 1987, they form a dynamic duo. Their two daughters, both music majors, have followed in their footsteps.
Together, Dennie and Krista make up the beloved two-piece band known as "Dennie and the Jets," which recently celebrated its 25th anniversary. When they're not performing gigs, you can find them sharing their musical talents at their local church in Mount Dora. Originally from Indianapolis, Krista has since made Tavares her home, where she continues to balance her career as a nurse with her love for music.

About Us
Ed Conlan is the proud owner and operator of The Back Room Steakhouse, a realization of his lifelong dream. His vision has always been to create a dining experience that combines top-notch quality with personalized service, all within a relaxed and unpretentious atmosphere. Our menu is centered around aged, black angus steaks, which serve as the foundation for a culinary journey that also includes fresh seafood, classic pasta dishes, unique appetizers, and delectable homemade desserts.
At The Back Room Steakhouse, we prioritize the use of fresh and high-quality ingredients in every meal we prepare. In addition to our exceptional food, we offer an extensive selection of fine wines, craft beers, signature craft cocktails, and a wide variety of spirits to perfectly complement your dining experience. We strive for perfection, but if for any reason you are not completely satisfied with your meal, please do not hesitate to reach out to Ed personally.
Thank you for choosing to visit us at The Back Room Steakhouse. It is an honor to have you as our guest, and we are eagerly looking forward to serving you and ensuring that your time with us is nothing short of extraordinary.
FAQâ€™s
What is your dress code?
We have a dress code at The Back Room Steakhouse that we like to refer to as "Nice Casual". We understand that our state has a very casual culture, and while we want our guests to feel comfortable, we also ask that they show respect for other patrons, especially since we often help celebrate special occasions such as birthdays and anniversaries.
For men, we encourage wearing a collared shirt. Dress jeans, shorts, and sandals are acceptable, but we kindly request no tank tops, ball caps, tee shirts, or flip flops.
Women are also kindly asked to refrain from wearing flip flops.
We hope you have a wonderful visit and we sincerely appreciate your cooperation in adhering to our dress code.
What should I expect?
As a small restaurant with a small kitchen, we highly recommend making a reservation to secure your table. While we do accept walk-ins, our tables tend to fill up quickly, especially on Friday and Saturday nights. If you prefer a quieter dining experience, Wednesday and Thursday nights are generally less busy, but we still suggest making a reservation to guarantee your spot.
To ensure that you have enough time to fully enjoy your meal, we have some general guidelines for meal service. For parties of two, a typical visit usually lasts around ninety minutes. This allows for a leisurely experience, including beverages, bread, salad, appetizers, entrees, and dessert. Larger parties may require more time, and our tables are paced accordingly to ensure that you can relax and savor each course. If you are in a rush or looking for a quick bite, we recommend visiting us when you have more time to fully appreciate the dining experience we offer.
At The Back Room Steakhouse, our motto is "fine dining in an unpretentious environment," and we take pride in providing attentive and personalized customer service. We strive to create a memorable dining experience for each and every guest. We hope that you can join us soon and allow us the opportunity to serve you.
Sincerely,
Ed Conlan
Owner/Operator

Our Team
Ed Conlan, Owner
Edâ€™s entire career has been focused on customer service with the past twenty years in the hospitality industry, specifically full-service restaurants. The Backroom Steakhouse concept came about as an idea to create a fine dining establishment featuring aged angus steaks, craft cocktails, with an extensive wine and craft beer selection Â served in an unpretentious environment with a focus on personalized service. Â The Backroom humbly opened their doors in Apopka inÂ 2001, an area not renowned for fine dining. It was a gambleâ€”but they slowly built a loyal following and expanded the restaurant after the first five years in business. Ed is especially proud of the awesome team he assembled including both the wait staff and culinary team who take tremendous pride in their work.
Ed is a hands-on owner operator and youâ€™ll find him making the rounds in an attempt to visit each table during our dinner service to ensure guest satisfaction.
Thomas Vitek (Chef Tommy), Executive Chef
Hailing from Allentown Pennsylvania, chef Tommy moved to Orlando with his family when he was 13.Â  at age 17, he went to work at the 94th arrows squadron restaurant. He worked there for six years moving up the ranks from dishwasher to lead line Cook in just two years. Next move was a 14 year stent at Interlachen country club. working under an Olympic culinary trained chef.
In 2004 he excepted his first executive chef position at Heathrow country club.Â  after five years at one of the busiest clubs in the state, it was time for a new challenge.
Eight years at Ginuwine bistro a casual concept created by his best friends, Chef Tommy built and designed the kitchen And menu from scratch to say it was a success is an understatement winning the taste of West Volusia five times in a row (Michael Jordan style ðŸ¤ª) was his crowning achievement
In 2019 at a chance meeting with Ed conlan, he was welcomed into the backroom steak house world, jumping at the idea of running a true steakhouse. With his dedicated staff he developed the back room kitchen and menu into the amazing experience It is today. The years have brought a lot of hard work and wonderful experiences and nothing delights Chef Tommy more than walking out into the dining room and seeing everyone truly enjoying their experience and, of course, the food.
Jennifer Camara, Front of the House Manager
Jennifer is Front of House Manager and Bar Lead at The Backroom Steakhouse. She is responsible for leading the staff and providing the best guest experience. Jennifer has been in the service industry for 20+ years and started her fine dining serving expertise here at Backroom in 2015. She is a customer favorite and is well-known and loved in the community. Just enter the doors of The Backroom Steakhouse and you will usually find her creating new, innovative cocktails, chatting with guests and keeping our standards high. Trust usâ€”sheâ€™s meticulous!
Service Staff
The front of the house team at The Backroom Steakhouse is not just passionate about serving you delicious food, but they also have serious love for their customers. Our team of dining superheroes is on a mission to make your time at The Backroom Steakhouse a stellar experience.
Kitchen Staff
The kitchen team behind the scenes at The Backroom Steakhouse is constantly pushing the boundaries of flavor, always on the lookout for new and exciting ingredients to elevate our menu to new heights.Â  From perfectly seared steaks to delectable sides and irresistible desserts, every dish is crafted with love and precision to ensure an unforgettable dining experience.
